                            <comment id="12482732" author="oysteing" created="Wed, 21 Mar 2007 12:20:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The batchUpdate test has recently been converted into Junit (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2293&quot; title=&quot;convert batchUpdate.java to junit&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-2293&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-2293&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), and the test is also run in client/server.  The test cases for batches of the PrepareStatementTest should probably be moved to the  BatchUpdateTest.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12996144" author="myrna" created="Thu, 17 Feb 2011 23:02:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking newcomer as the remaining task - moving the test cases for batches from the ParameterMappingTest (there&apos;s no batch stuff in PreparedStatementTest) to the BatchUpdateTest - ought to be fairly easy. But the tests are running where they are, so giving this low priority.&lt;br/&gt;
Or do we like them better in the ParameterMappingTest? After all, they&apos;re parameter mapping test cases too...And perhaps there&apos;s less code duplication if we leave them where they are... &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
